SECTION 0 -- GOVERNMENT AND PROHIBITED ENTITY RESTRICTION

This section supplements all other sections and takes precedence in
case of conflict.

a. "Prohibited Entity" means any of the following:

       1. Any national, federal, state, regional, or local government
          body, ministry, department, bureau, or agency;

       2. Any military organization, armed forces, or defense
          contractor primarily funded by a government;

       3. Any intelligence, surveillance, or law enforcement agency;

       4. Any political party, political campaign organization, or
          political action committee;

       5. Any entity that derives more than fifty percent (50%) of its
          annual funding from government sources (including grants,
          contracts, and subsidies), where such use is in furtherance
          of that entity's government-sponsored activities;

       6. Any private contractor, consultant, or third party acting
          directly on behalf of, at the direction of, or primarily in
          service of any of the entities listed above.

b. If You are a Prohibited Entity, or are acting on behalf of a
Prohibited Entity, You have no rights under this License. Any
exercise of the Licensed Rights by a Prohibited Entity is void
and constitutes a material breach of this License, automatically
terminating any rights that may have been granted.

c. For the avoidance of doubt, academic or research institutions
that receive partial government funding (e.g. public universities)
are NOT Prohibited Entities under this section, provided that the
use of the Licensed Material is solely for independent academic
research and is not conducted at the direction of a government
body or in direct service of a government contract.

